article.headline: UAB cruises into matchup with St. John's
article.linkText: Alabama-Birmingham gets past Siena in NIT
article.story:
ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Demario Eddins had 19 points and eight
rebounds to lead UAB past Siena 80-71 in the second round of the
Owens Corning NIT on Tuesday night.

	   Gabe Kennedy added 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Blazers
(21-12), who will play at St. John's (18-13) in the quarterfinals
on Thursday night.

	   After falling behind 53-44 with 15:09 left, Siena scored 11 of
the next 12 points to take a 55-54 lead. UAB regained the lead when
Eric Bush scored two quick buckets, and the Blazers didn't trail
again.

	   The Saints (21-11) tied the game four times, the last coming at
64-64, before UAB went on a 16-7 run in the final 5:58, sparked by
3-pointers from Morris Finley and Sidney Ball.

	   Michael Haddix led Siena with 16 points, while Antoine Jordan
and Tommy Mitchell added 12 points each. Prosper Karangwa had nine
points.

	   Bush had 15 points and two steals for UAB, establishing a new
Conference USA single-season record with 101 steals. Ball added 14
points and Finley had 13 points and eight assists.
